{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place garlic, mint, parsley, carrot, capsicum and 40 g of the red onion (cut into pieces) into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and curry powder and cook <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add mince, stock paste, tomato paste, water and pepper and cook <nobr>10-15 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr> or until meat is cooked. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Preheat oven to 220°C. Line 3 baking trays (approx. 30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Cut each sheet of pastry in half. Working with 1 piece at a time, create a border by scoring all edges (approx. 1 cm in from outer edge). Transfer pastry onto prepared trays. Prick all pastry sheets all over with a fork. Bake pastry for 3-4 minutes (220°C) or until bottom of pastry is partially cooked.","Divide mince mixture between pastry sheets, spreading a thin layer out to border of edges. Sprinkle with remaining 40 g red onion (cut into thin slices) and pine nuts. Brush pastry border with beaten egg and bake for 7-10 minutes (220°C) until pastry is crisp and golden.","Top tarts with desired ingredients (we used olives, feta, rocket and Lebanese cucumbers) (see Tips) to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["3 garlic cloves","8 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only","8 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","1 carrot, cut into pieces","100 g red capsicum, cut into pieces","80 g red onion, 40 g cut into thin slices and 40 g cut into pieces","20 g oil","1 tbsp curry powder","500 g beef mince","1 tbsp Chicken stock paste (see Tips)","2 tbsp tomato paste","40 g water","¼ tsp ground black pepper","4 - 5 sheets puff pastry (see Tips)","2 - 3 tbsp pine nuts","1 egg, lightly beaten","olives, to serve","feta cheese, to serve","rocket, to serve","Lebanese cucumber, to serve"]}],"id":"r238989","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-5kXk_YR5dsw\/XZQGWeKgKqI\/AAAAAAAAb9E\/iqT2_eXH6q